1
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:28,945
[Fisk] <i>Nadeem!</i>

2
00:00:30,238 --> 00:00:32,907
-[Fisk shouting]
-[gunshots and glass shattering]

3
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:36,161
[agent] <i>Stay in the car!</i>

4
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:38,913
[man 1] <i>Don't shoot! We surrender!</i>

5
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:41,624
[Dex] <i>Convict. Don't move.</i>

6
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:42,917
[sirens wailing]

7
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:47,922
[panting]

8
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:53,136
-[Ray] Move! Move!
-[officer] Get back! Back it up!

9
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:56,097
I need to make a call.

10
00:00:56,181 --> 00:00:57,307
Lobby's secure.

11
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:59,017
Straight to the nest! Move!

12
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:03,688
[Ray] SAC's inbound.
What the hell happened?

13
00:01:03,772 --> 00:01:04,814
[Dex] Ambush.

14
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:07,275
-They were everywhere.
-[Ray] Do you have status on anyone?

15
00:01:07,358 --> 00:01:10,987
[Dex] Two agents in surgery now.
We lost five for this shitbag.

16
00:01:14,282 --> 00:01:15,992
-[Fisk] Donovan!
-[Ray] Stay back.

17
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:18,870
-We're his attorneys.
-Congratulations. Stay back.

18
00:01:19,621 --> 00:01:20,872
Locate Vanessa.

19
00:01:21,664 --> 00:01:25,293
The Albanians, they tried to get me.
They'll go for her, too.

20
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:28,922
[Donovan] My client is not implying that
he knows how to reach a wanted fugitive.

21
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:30,632
And make sure she's safe!

22
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:43,895
[elevator dings]

23
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:48,274
[indistinct radio chatter]

24
00:01:50,568 --> 00:01:53,822
[sighs] We're good. Get the medic.

25
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:56,282
-[Dex] He's fine.
-[Ray] For me, not him.

26
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:58,952
Copy that. Shitbag's all yours.

27
00:01:59,035 --> 00:02:00,578
[Ray] Dex... Hold on.

28
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:03,957
Check in with the SAC.

29
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:07,001
[Dex] We're down too many agents.
The debrief can wait.

30
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:08,586
[Ray] You know the deal.

31
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:11,047
Follow the protocol
and get back here ASAP.

32
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:23,351
[Ray] You will be confined
to these quarters.

33
00:02:25,311 --> 00:02:27,605
You'll be monitored at all times.

34
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:31,693
You are allowed no outside contact
other than your lawyers.

35
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:35,113
Armed guards will be
stationed outside 24/7.

36
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:43,580
You'll be safe here.

37
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:47,041
"Safe." You nearly had me killed.

38
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:49,169
Good men died tonight.

39
00:02:50,044 --> 00:02:52,881
You will make their sacrifice
worth something.

40
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:57,260
Or you can shove our deal up your ass.

41
00:02:58,469 --> 00:03:00,096
[Arinori] <i>Hey, convict...</i>

42
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,265
your lawyers are here.

43
00:03:16,154 --> 00:03:17,155
Get dry.

44
00:03:17,238 --> 00:03:18,489
Get dressed.

45
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,287
[Fisk] Did you reach her?

46
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:26,998
I need these cameras shut off
and a moment with my client.

47
00:03:27,081 --> 00:03:30,043
-[Fisk] Forget about the cameras.
-[agent] Kill the cameras till they leave.

48
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:36,382
Is Vanessa safe? [Donovan] We don't know.

49
00:03:39,677 --> 00:03:41,054
She's missing.

50
00:03:45,266 --> 00:03:47,268
[theme music playing]

51
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:56,838
Oh, God. I don't know, it's been...
uh, three months since I had one.

52
00:04:56,921 --> 00:04:58,631
-See, now, that's bad.
-Yeah.

53
00:04:58,715 --> 00:05:00,925
Yeah, it's been about a month for me.

54
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:03,094
I've been elbows deep in, uh, research,

55
00:05:03,177 --> 00:05:05,722
but it feels like 100 years
since I had a home-cooked meal.

56
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:07,807
-This is all Uncle Mitchell.
-[Ellison] Please, stop.

57
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:10,435
Left to my own devices,
we'd be ordering Wo Hop every night.

58
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:13,521
-Nothing wrong with that.
-This woman does it all.

59
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:17,442
Not only does she run <i>Proxy Magazine,</i>
she is an expert orderer.

60
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:19,235
-Stop it.
-[Ellison] No, it's true.

61
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,112
You're amazing. It's like a skill.

62
00:05:21,195 --> 00:05:23,281
Right? You know all the best dishes
on every menu.

63
00:05:23,364 --> 00:05:25,783
You always order the right amount.
Never too much, too little.

64
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:26,993
[clicks tongue] It's perfect.

65
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:29,746
-[Lily] He'd be lost without me.
-[Ellison] I would.

66
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:32,332
-[Jason] Disgusting.
-Are they always like this?

67
00:05:32,915 --> 00:05:35,168
When I was eight,
they renewed their vows on Long Beach

68
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:36,836
-in front of the whole family.
-No.

69
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:39,130
Aunt Lily hired one of those planes
that write in the sky.

70
00:05:39,213 --> 00:05:42,467
-Oh, my God. Did you really? [chuckles]
-I did.

71
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:45,094
-So, how did you two meet?
-[Lily] Kind of like you guys, actually.

72
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:48,181
We were set up
by our college newspaper editor.

73
00:05:51,392 --> 00:05:54,437
-Oh. Mitchell, did you not tell them?
-[clears throat]

74
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,315
-[Jason] Uncle Mitchell...
-I am so sorry. I had no idea.

75
00:05:57,398 --> 00:05:59,692
I had no... I was--
I had nothing to do with it.

76
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,654
[sighs] You know what?
Uh, we need... We need more wine.

77
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:09,619
-Really?
-[stammers] I get it. I'm sorry.

78
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:10,578
-[scoffs]
-You know...

79
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:13,790
I knew that if I had actually asked you,
you'd have said no.

80
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:16,292
Right. See, that's the part
where it gets to be my choice.

81
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:17,794
I know you meant well, but this--

82
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:20,213
-You could use some happy.
-I am happy.

83
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:27,678
Look, I'm not, um... I'm not ready.

84
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:34,102
All right, well, if you want to leave,
I'll understand.

85
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,730
I'm sure Jason will, too.

86
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:42,485
[inhales and exhales deeply]

87
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:47,031
-[Karen laughs]
-[indistinct chatter]

88
00:06:47,949 --> 00:06:50,952
So, wait. You're telling me
that you named your cat Ralph?

89
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:52,745
-[Jason] Ellison.
-Oh.

90
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:56,541
Hey! I have a PhD in Am Lit.
He's my favorite author. "Life is to be lived, not controlled.
Humanity is won by--"

91
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,089
[Karen] I know this one, actually...

92
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:07,343
"Humanity is won by continuing to play
in the face of certain defeat."

93
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,428
Is that right?

94
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:10,346
How do you know the quote?

95
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,306
I was going to be an English major.

96
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:15,268
<i>Invisible Man</i> would have been
a big part of my curriculum,

97
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:18,020
but that was another lifetime. [chuckles]

98
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:19,522
[Jason] You made out okay.

99
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:22,191
A revered journalist
with an acclaimed publication.

100
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:24,152
-Okay.
-Too much, honey.

101
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:27,947
So, tell me, you ever worry
little Ralph's plotting your demise?

102
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:28,865
[Jason laughs]

103
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:31,868
-[Jason] I take it you're a dog person.
-Absolutely.

104
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:35,705
I don't know, I like the company.
Shared a room with my brother growing up.

105
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:38,332
The apartment felt empty till I got Ralph.

106
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:40,751
How about you? Any, uh, siblings?

107
00:07:42,086 --> 00:07:43,671
-Uh. More wine?
-Um...

108
00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:46,799
Yeah. No, I had a brother, too, but, um...

109
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:48,426
but he died.

110
00:07:48,509 --> 00:07:50,761
-[Jason] I'm sorry.
-No, it's okay.

111
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:54,682
-Who wants dessert?
-That'd be great. Thank you. [laughs]

112
00:07:54,765 --> 00:07:56,893
-[cell phone vibrating]
-[Ellison sighs]

113
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,770
Sorry. I'm sorry. Yeah. Ellison.

114
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:01,606
-[cell phone ringing]
-Uh, sorry.

115
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:06,986
Karen Page.

116
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:12,825
-Who in the hell would let out Fisk?
-[Ellison] Don't say his name.

117
00:08:12,909 --> 00:08:14,160
What? Why?

118
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:17,914
[sighs] After Ben died, Lily was
inconsolable. They were really close.

119
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:22,168
And, you know, it turned out that somebody
at my office had been working for him.

120
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:24,837
We'd gotten to the point where
an hour could go by,

121
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:27,215
and I didn't have to call
to reassure that I'm alive.

122
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:28,508
-I understand.
-Good.

123
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:32,678
Then you won't push back when I tell you,
you are staying away from this story.

124
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:34,055
[chuckles] I can't do that.

125
00:08:34,138 --> 00:08:36,015
Yes, you can. And you will.

126
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:38,351
Look, I get it.
I have a history with... that man.

127
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:40,061
-Makes it a conflict of interest.
-Exactly.

128
00:08:40,144 --> 00:08:42,396
But I also know him better
than anyone else on our staff.

129
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:45,483
-Doesn't that give me a unique angle?
-It gives you a bias. Look, it's not up for discussion.
Enjoy the pie.

130
00:08:51,989 --> 00:08:52,949
[door closes]

131
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:54,992
[sighs]

132
00:08:55,826 --> 00:08:58,704
[man on TV] <i>And, darling, that is not</i>
<i>a dress, that is a disaster.</i>

133
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:01,582
[woman on TV] <i>I worked on it with all</i>
<i>the materials available to me,</i>

134
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:03,584
<i>and I did the best with the time...</i>

135
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:04,794
[gasps]

136
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,129
[sighs] Baby...

137
00:09:10,299 --> 00:09:13,261
What was it this time? Laughing Matt?

138
00:09:15,304 --> 00:09:17,223
[inhales deeply] Body Matt.

139
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:23,854
Foggy Bear, whatever happened to Matt,
it's not your fault.

140
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:27,358
You have nothing to feel guilty about.

141
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:30,027
Because I have this great life?

142
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:34,448
Beautiful girlfriend, high-paying job,
expensive suits...

143
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:38,411
I always wanted a good suit.

144
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:42,373
I have it all, but Matt's just...

145
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,253
gone.

146
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,883
Maybe you should talk to someone.

147
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,053
It won't bring him back.

148
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:58,347
But it might help you.

149
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:04,979
[sighs] I can't.

150
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:07,523
Why not?

151
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:10,276
[exhales deeply]

152
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:16,115
Sorry. Go back to your brief.

153
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:22,496
Take a pill.
There's some in the medicine cabinet.

154
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:31,464
No. No. No.

155
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:39,597
[crowd chanting] Lock Fisk up!
Lock Fisk up!

156
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:43,267
Lock Fisk up! Lock Fisk up!

157
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,353
[chanting continues]

158
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,290
Doesn't make any sense.

159
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:12,463
Of course it does. God is angry with you.

160
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:15,675
What are you talking about?

161
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:21,305
You don't think God knows
you tried to kill yourself?

162
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:24,433
No.

163
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:28,437
That has nothing to do with this.

164
00:11:29,438 --> 00:11:31,524
God restored your hearing...

165
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:36,696
just in time to hear my name
chanted by the crowds.

166
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:41,617
Just in time to learn, in the long run,
I won, you lost.

167
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:44,745
Does that sound like God's forgiveness?

168
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:48,249
No.

169
00:11:49,625 --> 00:11:53,003
It sounds like... hell.

170
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:57,049
[crowd chanting] Lock Fisk up!
Lock Fisk up!

171
00:11:57,466 --> 00:11:59,635
[chanting continues]

172
00:12:00,761 --> 00:12:03,055
You'll never keep Karen safe.

173
00:12:06,308 --> 00:12:08,978
-In the end, you'll kill her, too.
-Stop it.

174
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:11,689
Just like your father.

175
00:12:11,772 --> 00:12:13,649
-And Stick.
-I said stop.

176
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,943
-And Elektra.
-[chuckles]

177
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,865
They all died because of you, Matthew.

178
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,541
[Karen] I can't believe this.
This is insane.

179
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,001
[officer] You're that reporter.

180
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,920
Sorry. Karen Page, <i>Bulletin.</i>

181
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:40,259
Uh... Sorry, who's in charge here?

182
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:44,305
That's the genius who got him out.
Agent Nadeem.

183
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:45,389
Thanks.

184
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:50,060
Agent Nadeem.

185
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:56,108
[Ray] Soon as I'm done here.
There's a vigil at the hospital.

186
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:59,320
Just give Sami a hug for me. You, too.

187
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:04,492
Hi. Karen Page of the <i>New York Bulletin.</i>

188
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:07,119
I'm not authorized to speak to the press.

189
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:09,455
You need to find
Special Agent In Charge Hattley.

190
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:11,665
But it is N-A-D-E-E-M, right?

191
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:13,751
And you're the agent
who released Wilson Fisk?

192
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:17,171
Fisk has not been released.
That's fake news.

193
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:19,048
-[chuckles]
-[Ray] He's a cooperating witness,

194
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:22,218
but he's very much a convicted prisoner
and being treated as such.

195
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:23,844
Being held in a $20 million penthouse?

196
00:13:23,928 --> 00:13:27,139
Seized by the US Government from some
Wall Street prick convicted of fraud.

197
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:29,683
Oh. Oh, I get it. Okay,
so what's he having for dinner?

198
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:32,853
Is it the filet mignon
or the line-caught halibut?

199
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:35,189
Press area is over there.

200
00:13:35,272 --> 00:13:37,900
[Karen] One RICO count carries
a 20-year sentence.

201
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:42,655
Fisk was convicted on five.
Want to explain to me how this is justice?

202
00:13:45,658 --> 00:13:48,619
Jennings, Garcia, Foster,
Leighton, Torres.

203
00:13:49,286 --> 00:13:52,456
They lost their lives,
and they were good agents, good people.

204
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,334
Write about that, Ms. Page.

205
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,681
[man 1] All right...

206
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:10,850
get it up there.

207
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:13,853
-[man 1] All right?
-[man 2] Yeah. Okay.

208
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,066
[man 1] Excuse us. Watch yourself.

209
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:24,780
[keypad beeping]

210
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,657
-[door buzzes]
-Nine-one-seven-four.

211
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:48,846
[keypad beeping]

212
00:14:48,929 --> 00:14:50,598
[door rattles]

213
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:55,603
[door buzzes]

214
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:00,858
[Matt] Thanks.

215
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:13,537
Oh. Hey, man, hand me one of those BNCs,
would ya?

216
00:15:18,042 --> 00:15:21,545
Thanks. Dude, I said a BNC...

217
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:31,805
[man 1] Yes, I've checked three times.
I have the tickets.

218
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:34,099
[woman 1] Okay, okay.
I just wanted to be sure.

219
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:37,186
With this mess outside,
we don't wanna have to come back.

220
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:46,654
-[woman 2] Do you think we're safe?
-[man 2] We should check out.

221
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:49,490
[man 3] We booked this months ago.
Now we have to deal with this?

222
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:50,866
[man 4] We're checking out early.

223
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,868
[desk clerk] We are very sorry
for the disruption.

224
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,037
Can we assist you in making
reservations elsewhere?

225
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,498
[man 4] Do you know who I am?
You know who he is, right?

226
00:15:57,581 --> 00:15:58,999
[desk clerk] Just one moment, sir.

227
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:05,255
[agent 1 over radio] <i>Watch rotation.</i>
<i>Sound off.</i>

228
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:07,925
[agent 2 over radio] <i>North entrance</i>
<i>is green.</i>

229
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:10,552
[agent 3 over radio] <i>West entrance</i>
<i>is green.</i>

230
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:12,262
[agent 4 over radio] <i>Service area</i>
<i>is green.</i>

231
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:16,725
[Doyle] Lobby is green.

232
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:27,069
So, you're inside. Now what?

233
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:29,530
Why would they let you out?

234
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:31,657
Does it matter?

235
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:35,703
The real question is, when you find me,
what are you prepared to do?

236
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:39,206
See, if the FBI are protecting you,
that means you cut a deal.

237
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:43,711
With everything I know
about crime in this city...

238
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,296
the FBI will be eating out of my hand.

239
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:48,924
-You'll manipulate them.
-You don't know that.

240
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:50,843
[chuckles] I know you.

241
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:54,221
Maybe prison has changed me.

242
00:16:54,304 --> 00:16:56,515
-[laughs]
<i>-</i>[Fisk] Maybe right this moment

243
00:16:56,598 --> 00:16:59,893
I'm giving the FBI information
that will save lives.

244
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:04,398
While you're here doing what?
Whatever this is.

245
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:07,985
-Wouldn't that be something?
-[clicks tongue]

246
00:17:08,068 --> 00:17:11,572
[Fisk] If I became more valuable
to this city than you ever were.

247
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:53,697
[Lim] Garcia was the best man
at my wedding. Word is Andrews will pull through.

248
00:17:57,534 --> 00:18:00,746
If you call probably never going
to walk again pulling through.

249
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:04,208
[sighs]

250
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:07,878
That's hard. That's really hard.

251
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:11,298
[Lim] And he gets a penthouse.

252
00:18:14,551 --> 00:18:18,472
Shut the cameras off, please.
We need time with our client.

253
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,561
[clears throat]

254
00:18:33,862 --> 00:18:34,988
And?

255
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:37,449
[Donovan] We reached Felix Manning.
Vanessa's safe.

256
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:40,119
Her bodyguards
relocate her every 72 hours,

257
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:43,205
and they take precautions
to avoid being tracked.

258
00:18:43,288 --> 00:18:46,083
No cell phones.
It's why they were unreachable.

259
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:47,251
Where is she now?

260
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:49,837
[Lee] A safe house outside Barcelona.

261
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:56,802
Felix hid her in Spain?

262
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:58,387
[Donovan] It was her decision.

263
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:02,141
We strongly advised against Europe,
given the extradition risk,

264
00:19:02,224 --> 00:19:06,145
but Ms. Marianna enjoys the art
and she can be very insistent.

265
00:19:10,524 --> 00:19:13,402
Yes, she can.

266
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:20,367
But it's too easy for the Albanians
to get at her there.

267
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:23,537
Call Felix.

268
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:28,000
Tell him to put Vanessa some place safer.

269
00:19:29,751 --> 00:19:31,336
Some place closer.

270
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,342
 [exhales sharply]

271
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:59,656
[Tower] "Homicides are down,
burglaries down, assaults down.

272
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:01,825
I have not accomplished this alone.

273
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:04,912
The good people of Hell's Kitchen
have said no more.

274
00:20:04,995 --> 00:20:07,122
Together with the NYPD,

275
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:09,583
we have begun to take
our neighborhoods back.

276
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:14,213
Reelect me for district attorney,
and let's continue to take our city back.

277
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,923
Together."

278
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:19,218
How was that?

279
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:21,511
Too many "togethers."
Sounds like a Beatles' song.

280
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:23,430
[Tower] Okay, but is that good?

281
00:20:23,513 --> 00:20:24,514
[Arlene] No.

282
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:31,355
-Wow. I'm inspired.
-[Tower] Mr. Nelson.

283
00:20:31,438 --> 00:20:33,732
[Arlene] Mr. Tower, you need to get ready.

284
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:37,110
I believe a $1,500 contribution
buys me ten minutes.

285
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:39,947
It doesn't buy you anything,
but I'll give you five.

286
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:42,449
-Arlene, I said the blue one.
-It had a stain.

287
00:20:42,532 --> 00:20:44,785
The charcoal's the ticket. Trust me.

288
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:46,453
You have five minutes.

289
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:51,166
So, what can I do for you?

290
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:53,794
It's what I can do for you.

291
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:56,463
The Wilson Fisk case.

292
00:20:56,546 --> 00:21:00,801
I want to provide my complete,
unmitigated, fully caffeinated support.

293
00:21:00,884 --> 00:21:02,135
I'm sorry, the Fisk case?

294
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:04,221
I know you're doing
everything in your power

295
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:06,640
to reverse the terms
of that crap deal he finagled.

296
00:21:06,723 --> 00:21:09,434
But you're under-resourced
and I'm over-resourced.

297
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:12,604
Like, obscenely over-resourced.

298
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:16,858
All this to say, I'm drafting myself
onto your team for this.

299
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,944
So tag me the hell in.

300
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:22,864
Maybe just a nod?

301
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:24,783
-[chuckles] Mr. Nelson--
-Foggy.

302
00:21:24,866 --> 00:21:26,576
I already fought this tooth and nail.

303
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:29,037
I objected to Mr. Fisk's
house incarceration

304
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:30,914
on every ground imaginable.

305
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:32,416
I assumed as much.

306
00:21:32,499 --> 00:21:35,711
So I did some digging,
and if we can open a state case,

307
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:37,546
we can at least put him back behind bars.

308
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:40,632
At least for a while,
which will buy us time to build--

309
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:41,967
It's just not feasible.

310
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:46,763
I'll do research. Late-night strategizing.
All pro bono, of course. Soup to nuts.

311
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:49,391
Nelson reporting for duty, sir.

312
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:51,977
Fisk is cooperating
with the federal government.

313
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:54,354
There's nothing I can do.

314
00:21:54,938 --> 00:21:58,317
I know you know the difference
between a good fight and a losing battle.

315
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:01,028
I know that sometimes
they're the same thing.

316
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:03,947
And you don't know which battle
you're fighting until you're fighting it.

317
00:22:04,031 --> 00:22:05,240
Well, I'm moving on.

318
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:07,034
You should, too.

319
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:10,495
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have to go change for an interview.

320
00:22:10,579 --> 00:22:13,165
So that's it? You're just gonna roll over?

321
00:22:13,248 --> 00:22:16,460
No, I'm just gonna do my job.
And your five minutes are up.

322
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:20,088
Would you care more
if you weren't trying to get reelected?

323
00:22:20,172 --> 00:22:21,381
Watch it, Counselor.

324
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:23,258
Fisk had Ms. Cardenas killed.

325
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:27,554
Maybe you don't give a damn,
because she's dead and can't vote for you,

326
00:22:27,637 --> 00:22:29,890
but she was a good person.

327
00:22:29,973 --> 00:22:34,686
She cared about her community,
was braver than both of us put together.

328
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:37,314
Fisk will hurt more people like her.

329
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:42,069
She didn't have a voice,
because the people in power didn't care.

330
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:44,738
You're supposed to be
Ms. Cardenas's voice.

331
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:51,411
Leave... or I'm calling security.

332
00:22:54,247 --> 00:22:55,582
I'm going.

333
00:22:56,541 --> 00:22:58,418
But I'm canceling my check.

334
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:05,258
[crowd chanting] Prison, not a penthouse!
Prison, not a penthouse!

335
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:07,552
[chanting continues]

336
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:13,683
Chow is on the way, guys.

337
00:23:23,443 --> 00:23:24,945
[Dex] Mickey D's?

338
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:28,740
[Doyle] You think DOJ is going to cover
$40 tuna melts for us?

339
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:30,325
Just a coffee, please.

340
00:23:30,409 --> 00:23:32,369
[Dex] Save me something. I'm up in ten.

341
00:23:33,703 --> 00:23:34,955
[Doyle] Penthouse, please.

342
00:23:36,623 --> 00:23:39,418
-[Fisk] It's got the best view.
-[sighs]

343
00:23:40,293 --> 00:23:41,837
You should be rotting in a cell.

344
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:44,297
So you're gonna bring me back to prison?

345
00:23:46,466 --> 00:23:48,260
But you know that won't work.

346
00:23:51,346 --> 00:23:54,474
There's only one way to stop me,
but you're not gonna do it.

347
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:56,977
Are you sure about that?

348
00:23:57,644 --> 00:23:59,229
In a way, you're my accomplice.

349
00:23:59,312 --> 00:24:03,942
Everything that's happened
since you refused to kill me is on you.

350
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:07,529
The bodies that I've stacked up.

351
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:10,240
The ones to come.

352
00:24:11,825 --> 00:24:14,453
-I wonder who's next?
-[Donovan] You have the routing number.

353
00:24:15,579 --> 00:24:17,998
Two million. In euros.

354
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:22,252
No, today. My client is not a patient man.

355
00:24:22,335 --> 00:24:26,256
[Fisk] You can follow him right to me.
You know you want to.

356
00:24:34,097 --> 00:24:36,308
-May I see your room key, sir?
-Yeah, I got it.

357
00:24:36,391 --> 00:24:37,767
No, I need to see it.

358
00:24:38,351 --> 00:24:39,769
Oh, sure. Yeah.

359
00:24:39,853 --> 00:24:41,688
[Fisk] You can take him. Grab his gun.

360
00:24:42,689 --> 00:24:45,609
Come for me. I'm caged up. Unarmed.

361
00:24:45,692 --> 00:24:48,570
-Sir.
-They gave me, like, three of them.

362
00:24:48,653 --> 00:24:49,821
[Fisk] But you won't.

363
00:24:51,406 --> 00:24:55,368
You can't kill me.
You can't even kill yourself.

364
00:24:57,454 --> 00:24:59,915
You know what?
I must have left it in my car.

365
00:24:59,998 --> 00:25:01,625
Then I can't let you through.

366
00:25:03,877 --> 00:25:05,086
Sure, I...

367
00:25:05,879 --> 00:25:07,339
I'll be right back.

368
00:25:14,095 --> 00:25:16,973
[man over PA] <i>Pharmacy service,</i>
<i>please call station four.</i>

369
00:25:17,057 --> 00:25:19,809
<i>Pharmacy service,</i>
<i>please call station four.</i>

370
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:22,270
[woman sobbing]

371
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:33,490
[woman over PA]<i> Doctor Brenner, 241.</i>

372
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:40,038
[softly] I'm so sorry.

373
00:25:48,922 --> 00:25:50,006
Hey, boss.

374
00:25:51,841 --> 00:25:55,971
Andrews is back under the knife.
They think they can save his liver.

375
00:25:58,098 --> 00:26:00,767
Good. Good. That's good.

376
00:26:01,935 --> 00:26:04,854
I wanted to give blood, but...

377
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:07,732
I wasn't sure if I should show my face.

378
00:26:09,109 --> 00:26:10,777
Nobody blames you.

379
00:26:10,860 --> 00:26:12,279
I blame me.

380
00:26:12,362 --> 00:26:13,989
Moving Fisk was my call.

381
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:15,991
Because I pushed for it.

382
00:26:16,074 --> 00:26:18,410
Because it was the smart thing to do.

383
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:22,998
Because we signed up to protect people.

384
00:26:23,832 --> 00:26:26,126
And this is what it looks like sometimes.

385
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:29,671
Think of all the times this won't happen
because of what we're doing.

386
00:26:29,754 --> 00:26:32,090
Not to civilians. Not to us.

387
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:36,303
Hold on to all the lives we're saving.

388
00:26:38,179 --> 00:26:41,933
They matter...
just as much as the one's we've lost.

389
00:26:46,688 --> 00:26:47,689
Yeah.

390
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:24,351
<i>Bon appétit,</i> asshole.

391
00:27:29,105 --> 00:27:31,733
[inhales and exhales deeply]

392
00:27:38,573 --> 00:27:41,701
It's Special Agent Poindexter, isn't it?

393
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:46,331
You saved my life last night.

394
00:27:46,414 --> 00:27:48,541
Yeah, we all make mistakes.

395
00:27:52,671 --> 00:27:55,298
I'm sorry for the loss
of your fellow agents.

396
00:27:56,883 --> 00:27:59,803
Losing them to protect someone like me...

397
00:28:01,137 --> 00:28:07,268
must be particularly difficult
for the families and the loved ones.

398
00:28:10,063 --> 00:28:12,148
I'd offer my condolences...

399
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:16,695
but I imagine it brings them
greater comfort to hate me.

400
00:28:21,449 --> 00:28:23,660
Unless you feel otherwise.

401
00:28:24,577 --> 00:28:27,956
That my words might bring
any positive effect.

402
00:28:28,957 --> 00:28:32,127
If so, please share that,
from what I witnessed,

403
00:28:33,044 --> 00:28:35,046
they were incredibly brave.

404
00:28:35,130 --> 00:28:38,466
Might wanna eat faster, convict.
The meal's over in five.

405
00:28:40,135 --> 00:28:44,889
I owe those fallen agents a debt...

406
00:28:47,475 --> 00:28:48,977
that I can never repay.

407
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:54,065
But...

408
00:28:57,277 --> 00:28:59,320
I also owe you.

409
00:29:01,823 --> 00:29:05,326
I've known extraordinary people.

410
00:29:06,578 --> 00:29:09,622
But I've never seen a talent like yours.

411
00:29:12,709 --> 00:29:16,838
May I ask you where you acquired
such a skill?

412
00:29:17,589 --> 00:29:20,175
Okay. You're done.

413
00:29:32,187 --> 00:29:34,189
[Dex]<i> I saved him 'cause it was my job.</i>

414
00:29:34,272 --> 00:29:35,857
What more do you want me to say, Doc?

415
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:39,027
Forget Fisk. Talk to me about the ambush.

416
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:41,821
What about it?

417
00:29:42,447 --> 00:29:44,741
Come on, Poindexter,
we both know how this works.

418
00:29:44,824 --> 00:29:47,202
We have to talk
so I can clear you for duty.

419
00:29:47,285 --> 00:29:48,286
It is what it is.

420
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:51,289
I lost friends today.

421
00:29:51,372 --> 00:29:54,042
And you used lethal force
against multiple suspects.

422
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:55,418
-Yeah.
-And you're on duty

423
00:29:55,502 --> 00:29:57,420
even though you should be
on administrative leave.

424
00:29:57,504 --> 00:29:59,297
I understand you're trying to do your job,

425
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:02,467
but if I were wearing a mask,
the press would be calling me a hero.

426
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:05,678
Instead, I'm sitting here
trying to justify protecting myself.

427
00:30:05,762 --> 00:30:07,972
I'm not the enemy. I'm just trying to...

428
00:30:09,224 --> 00:30:12,185
Look, forget the psych bullshit
for a minute.

429
00:30:12,268 --> 00:30:16,272
Just tell me for real, how are you?

430
00:30:22,195 --> 00:30:23,571
It's hard.

431
00:30:24,364 --> 00:30:26,074
It's really hard.

432
00:30:26,157 --> 00:30:29,327
This isn't the first time
you've used lethal force.

433
00:30:29,410 --> 00:30:33,206
I'm FBI SWAT, Doc.
What do you think a sniper does?

434
00:30:33,748 --> 00:30:36,876
Well, the thing is, Dex...
Can I call you Dex?

435
00:30:37,460 --> 00:30:41,172
The thing is,
events like this exact a toll.

436
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:44,801
Repeating traumatic experiences
compounds that toll, creating a pressure.

437
00:30:44,884 --> 00:30:47,220
Until one day I go postal? Yeah, I get it.

438
00:30:47,303 --> 00:30:50,223
The point is,
you have to process this stuff.

439
00:30:50,306 --> 00:30:51,558
I process it.

440
00:30:51,641 --> 00:30:53,518
Do you have a support system?

441
00:30:54,561 --> 00:30:57,397
Well, I think
she'd rather be called Julie.

442
00:30:57,981 --> 00:31:00,692
Oh. Well, tell me, how does that work?

443
00:31:02,735 --> 00:31:04,153
She's a bartender.

444
00:31:04,863 --> 00:31:06,781
Professional listener, like you.

445
00:31:07,490 --> 00:31:09,033
She probably gets paid more.

446
00:31:09,117 --> 00:31:09,993
[chuckles]

447
00:31:11,744 --> 00:31:13,162
Tell me about her.

448
00:31:13,246 --> 00:31:15,081
We get dinner most nights.

449
00:31:15,665 --> 00:31:17,208
Today's Tuesday?

450
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:19,002
It's pizza night.

451
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:23,006
Julie gets broccoli with sausage,
extra cheese.

452
00:31:23,089 --> 00:31:24,716
I tell her about my day.

453
00:31:25,466 --> 00:31:27,051
The good, the bad.

454
00:31:27,135 --> 00:31:30,305
I know it's not healthy
to hold this stuff in, so...

455
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:31,764
I talk to her.

456
00:31:32,473 --> 00:31:33,975
I tell her everything.

457
00:31:35,268 --> 00:31:36,144
And...

458
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:39,689
And she doesn't judge me or blame me.

459
00:31:40,398 --> 00:31:43,276
She's just... there for me.

460
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:46,529
She sounds like a good one.

461
00:31:47,947 --> 00:31:49,198
Yeah, she is.

462
00:31:53,369 --> 00:31:55,955
All right. You are clear for duty.

463
00:31:56,039 --> 00:32:00,501
But I want you checking in with me daily
for a while. Okay?

464
00:32:00,585 --> 00:32:01,836
Yes, sir.

465
00:32:02,837 --> 00:32:07,300
You, uh... You go see your girl.
It'll do you good.

466
00:32:22,982 --> 00:32:24,233
[Donovan grunts]

467
00:32:29,864 --> 00:32:32,158
Why did Fisk flip on the Albanians?

468
00:32:32,241 --> 00:32:36,204
I don't know what you're talking about.
You've got the wrong person. [gasps]

469
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:41,000
Fisk hated prison. The FBI got him out.

470
00:32:41,084 --> 00:32:44,170
No, no. He could have turned on anyone.
Why the Albanians?

471
00:32:44,253 --> 00:32:45,630
I'm just a lawyer.

472
00:32:45,713 --> 00:32:49,926
What is Fisk really getting out of this?
Is it the Albanians' territory?

473
00:32:50,009 --> 00:32:51,719
-No.
-Is it money?

474
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:52,804
No.

475
00:32:53,972 --> 00:32:56,516
Why don't you let me know
when you wanna breathe?

476
00:32:56,599 --> 00:32:57,976
[groans]

477
00:33:00,436 --> 00:33:01,854
Fisk's woman.

478
00:33:02,522 --> 00:33:04,273
The feds will drop
all charges against her.

479
00:33:04,357 --> 00:33:07,902
-No.
-I swear! He's doing it all for her.

480
00:33:08,861 --> 00:33:11,656
[heart beating steadily]

481
00:33:12,907 --> 00:33:14,242
And where is Vanessa?

482
00:33:14,325 --> 00:33:17,036
-[agent 1] Where you wanna eat?
-[agent 2] How about the Chinese place?

483
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:19,914
-[Donovan] Help! Help!
-[agent 3] Over there! Go! Let's go!

484
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:20,999
[Donovan] Help!

485
00:33:22,709 --> 00:33:24,210
He's an Albanian.

486
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:27,964
[agent 4] There's an unidentified
assailant in the parking deck,

487
00:33:28,047 --> 00:33:29,757
considered armed and dangerous.

488
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:30,758
[gun cocking]

489
00:33:40,685 --> 00:33:41,561
[grunts]

490
00:33:41,936 --> 00:33:43,021
[gasping]

491
00:33:43,104 --> 00:33:44,731
[agent 5] Anyone got a visual on him?

492
00:33:45,523 --> 00:33:48,317
[agent 6 over radio] <i>Nothing yet.</i>
<i>Moving to the south side of the garage.</i>

493
00:34:06,794 --> 00:34:07,754
[grunts]

494
00:34:20,933 --> 00:34:23,895
[agent 6] We're in stairwell H,
heading down to parking level three.

495
00:34:28,775 --> 00:34:31,027
[agent 2] We need backup
on parking level three.

496
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:34,030
Repeat, we need backup
on parking level three.

497
00:34:37,116 --> 00:34:39,118
-[agent] Stop! FBI!
-[Matt panting]

498
00:34:39,702 --> 00:34:41,329
They have families, asshole.

499
00:34:41,412 --> 00:34:43,372
Listen. I'm not here to...

500
00:34:46,375 --> 00:34:47,794
[both grunting]

501
00:34:47,877 --> 00:34:50,963
-There he is! Stop! Stop!
-[agent] Stop!

502
00:34:51,047 --> 00:34:52,673
[gunshots]

503
00:34:54,133 --> 00:34:56,719
Come out with your hands up. Now.

504
00:34:57,553 --> 00:34:58,387
[grunting]

505
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:20,493
Stay down, man.

506
00:35:25,832 --> 00:35:27,834
[panting]

507
00:35:30,837 --> 00:35:31,963
Oh, God.

508
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:36,008
That's it. Let the Devil out.

509
00:35:46,102 --> 00:35:49,689
Felt good, didn't it?
Too bad you still can't get at me.

510
00:35:49,772 --> 00:35:51,941
Not with the FBI protecting me.

511
00:35:53,151 --> 00:35:57,655
I'm going to kill everyone you love,
and there's nothing you can do about it.

512
00:36:27,476 --> 00:36:28,811
Paper goes to bed in 20 minutes.

513
00:36:28,895 --> 00:36:31,063
-You got 15 seconds.
-Okay. It's big.

514
00:36:31,189 --> 00:36:32,607
-Shit. Fisk.
-No, look--

515
00:36:32,690 --> 00:36:35,318
God damn it.
I explicitly told you not to do that.

516
00:36:35,401 --> 00:36:37,111
-I didn't set out to.
-Stop.

517
00:36:37,195 --> 00:36:39,363
Mason saw you at the hotel.

518
00:36:39,906 --> 00:36:44,452
I mean, I know Fisk is important to you.
I know. I don't care. Okay?

519
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:46,746
I assign the stories,
and I gave this one to Mason.

520
00:36:46,829 --> 00:36:50,291
I wasn't there on that story.
I was there on my story. Kazemis?

521
00:36:51,876 --> 00:36:53,628
Look, I think there's a connection.

522
00:36:54,378 --> 00:36:55,379
What do you mean?

523
00:36:55,463 --> 00:36:57,423
Do you know who used to own
the Presidential Hotel?

524
00:36:57,506 --> 00:36:59,133
-No.
-The Kazemis.

525
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:01,969
I don't have proof yet,
but you know who I think owns it now?

526
00:37:03,054 --> 00:37:04,138
Wilson Fisk.

527
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:15,524
-Tell me.
-Okay.

528
00:37:15,608 --> 00:37:17,151
Look, I got a lead.

529
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:21,155
So the Presidential Hotel is owned
by these nested shell companies.

530
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:23,616
It's just one company
who owns another and another...

531
00:37:23,699 --> 00:37:27,328
Anyway, I tracked them from here
to the Caymans to Luxembourg.

532
00:37:27,411 --> 00:37:28,746
And this connects to Fisk how?

533
00:37:28,829 --> 00:37:30,206
Because all of those companies,

534
00:37:30,289 --> 00:37:33,626
they're all represented here
in the United States by one law firm.

535
00:37:33,709 --> 00:37:35,211
Donovan and Partners.

536
00:37:36,212 --> 00:37:37,505
Fisk's lawyers.

537
00:37:39,548 --> 00:37:40,549
Okay, keep going.

538
00:37:40,633 --> 00:37:42,343
All right,
here's what I've pieced together.

539
00:37:42,969 --> 00:37:44,136
Six months ago,

540
00:37:44,220 --> 00:37:48,391
one of these shell companies buys
the Presidential Hotel from Kazemi.

541
00:37:48,474 --> 00:37:51,686
A week ago, he tells his family
that he regrets the sale

542
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:54,438
and announces his intention
to buy the hotel back.

543
00:37:54,522 --> 00:37:56,983
And two days later, Kazemi gets attacked.

544
00:37:57,066 --> 00:38:00,528
Yes. Yes, exactly. Now,
I don't think that timing is coincidental.

545
00:38:00,611 --> 00:38:01,696
I just...

546
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:05,741
I can feel Fisk is behind this.
Right? I feel it in my bones.

547
00:38:05,825 --> 00:38:09,287
I need two days to get everything vetted,
then I'll have a story that you can run.

548
00:38:10,621 --> 00:38:13,416
-It's excellent. Outstanding work, Karen.
-Thank you.

549
00:38:13,499 --> 00:38:14,500
Really.

550
00:38:14,583 --> 00:38:16,002
Yeah. [clears throat]

551
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:20,589
-I'm giving it to Mason. I told you.
-What? No, I know, I'm biased.

552
00:38:20,673 --> 00:38:23,968
Of course! Of course I'm biased.
Fisk tried to have me killed.

553
00:38:24,051 --> 00:38:26,721
He also killed Ben,
which makes you as biased as me.

554
00:38:26,804 --> 00:38:30,349
If people see your name
and know your connection to Fisk,

555
00:38:30,433 --> 00:38:32,935
it compromises this paper!

556
00:38:33,019 --> 00:38:36,814
Fine. Give the byline to Mason.
I don't give a shit about credit.

557
00:38:36,897 --> 00:38:39,150
What I give a shit about
is Fisk getting out of prison.

558
00:38:39,775 --> 00:38:43,321
We have to do something...
I have to do something about this.

559
00:38:43,404 --> 00:38:45,364
So don't tell me to back off,
'cause I won't.

560
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:52,913
You know, it took Ben decades
to become this much of a pain in my ass.

561
00:38:59,211 --> 00:39:00,046
[exhales deeply]

562
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:02,256
[typing] [footsteps approaching]

563
00:39:19,148 --> 00:39:21,108
Well, at least you're upright.

564
00:39:27,365 --> 00:39:29,909
[sighs] Do I even wanna know?

565
00:39:34,163 --> 00:39:36,123
Do you believe people can change?

566
00:39:37,541 --> 00:39:39,794
I'm still holding out hope.

567
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:44,131
I don’t think we can.

568
00:39:45,633 --> 00:39:46,717
Not really.

569
00:39:49,345 --> 00:39:51,847
I think we come into this world
who we are.

570
00:39:53,015 --> 00:39:55,142
And maybe we get a little nicer.

571
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:57,978
Or a little angrier.

572
00:40:00,356 --> 00:40:02,858
But we can't change
our fundamental nature.

573
00:40:07,571 --> 00:40:10,116
[Maggie] Well, you'd actually
have to try to know.

574
00:40:10,866 --> 00:40:13,077
[Matt] I was talking about Wilson Fisk.

575
00:40:14,995 --> 00:40:17,123
So your hearing's really back, then?

576
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:22,002
Well, what do you know?
Maybe the boss did hear my prayers.

577
00:40:22,962 --> 00:40:24,588
Yeah, or my curses.

578
00:40:24,672 --> 00:40:26,715
Please don't start with Job again.

579
00:40:28,467 --> 00:40:31,262
You gotta admit it's interesting,
though, isn't it?

580
00:40:31,345 --> 00:40:33,681
I finally get my full hearing back,

581
00:40:33,764 --> 00:40:37,101
and the first thing I hear
is that Wilson Fisk is out of prison.

582
00:40:37,726 --> 00:40:42,273
So you're suggesting that God set a
dangerous mobster free just to spite you?

583
00:40:45,192 --> 00:40:46,193
Nah.

584
00:40:47,361 --> 00:40:49,196
Probably just a coincidence.

585
00:40:50,030 --> 00:40:52,867
Because that would be
incredibly narcissistic.

586
00:40:54,952 --> 00:40:56,328
[Matt sniffs]

587
00:40:59,623 --> 00:41:02,168
Fisk claims to be helping the FBI.

588
00:41:03,085 --> 00:41:05,087
But they don't know him like I do.

589
00:41:05,838 --> 00:41:09,758
Right. And according to you,
people can't change.

590
00:41:11,385 --> 00:41:12,219
[sighs]

591
00:41:12,845 --> 00:41:15,764
'Cause he's claiming
to have changed over a woman.

592
00:41:16,432 --> 00:41:17,558
I see.

593
00:41:19,435 --> 00:41:24,023
Well, if there's anything
that can redeem a lost soul,

594
00:41:25,024 --> 00:41:26,609
love would have to top the list.

595
00:41:26,692 --> 00:41:28,777
Oh, come on. Even a monster like Fisk?

596
00:41:29,778 --> 00:41:31,989
You're talking to a nun, kiddo.

597
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:35,117
Love and redemption
are pretty much our sales pitch.

598
00:41:35,201 --> 00:41:36,619
Yeah. Well, I'm not buying.

599
00:41:38,662 --> 00:41:40,247
So, what are you gonna do?

600
00:41:44,001 --> 00:41:45,169
I don't know.

601
00:41:47,922 --> 00:41:49,423
Maybe I'll stop him.

602
00:41:51,550 --> 00:41:52,843
For good this time.

603
00:41:59,183 --> 00:42:03,103
Well, just be careful
that you don't become the monster.

604
00:42:29,922 --> 00:42:31,298
[footsteps approaching]

605
00:43:04,540 --> 00:43:05,541
[chuckles softly]

606
00:43:42,036 --> 00:43:44,913
-[soft rock music playing]
-[indistinct chatter]

607
00:44:10,606 --> 00:44:11,649
[whispering] Foggy.

608
00:44:16,028 --> 00:44:17,446
This isn't real.

609
00:44:20,032 --> 00:44:21,033
It's real.

610
00:44:22,743 --> 00:44:23,577
[chuckles]

611
00:44:27,289 --> 00:44:28,540
Hey, Foggy.

612
00:44:29,041 --> 00:44:32,211
How? Where have...
We all thought you were dead.

613
00:44:33,212 --> 00:44:34,296
I'm sorry.

614
00:44:35,714 --> 00:44:38,425
-Does Karen know you're back yet?
-Take a seat.

615
00:44:40,386 --> 00:44:41,387
I'm...

616
00:44:42,971 --> 00:44:44,348
I'm not back.

617
00:44:44,973 --> 00:44:49,770
-Well, I'm 75% sure I'm not hallucinating.
-[clears throat] I'm, uh... not back.

618
00:44:52,022 --> 00:44:54,858
Matt Murdock isn't gonna be
a part of me anymore. Um...

619
00:44:55,943 --> 00:44:58,445
-I'm leaving him behind.
-What?

620
00:44:58,529 --> 00:45:02,950
The only reason I came here
was to warn you and Karen...

621
00:45:03,826 --> 00:45:06,328
that Fisk is out
and you're both in danger. -Dude--
-I've had a rough couple of months, Foggy.

622
00:45:10,124 --> 00:45:11,500
Questioning a lot of...

623
00:45:13,752 --> 00:45:15,045
The point of it all.

624
00:45:16,964 --> 00:45:19,341
And last night, everything became clear.

625
00:45:21,343 --> 00:45:25,431
I'm going after him, Foggy.
I'm gonna find a way to bring Fisk down.

626
00:45:25,514 --> 00:45:28,058
But I can only do that
if I know you and Karen are safe.

627
00:45:28,142 --> 00:45:29,852
[chuckles] Dude, slow down.

628
00:45:29,935 --> 00:45:32,813
I'm still processing that you're,
like, even sitting here.

629
00:45:32,896 --> 00:45:34,815
I know you're gonna want to get involved.

630
00:45:35,858 --> 00:45:38,986
You and Karen will try and fight Fisk
in some way.

631
00:45:39,069 --> 00:45:40,154
I'm telling you,

632
00:45:40,946 --> 00:45:43,741
I need you to stay out of it
and leave it to me.

633
00:45:46,910 --> 00:45:47,911
No.

634
00:45:49,496 --> 00:45:51,123
-"No"?
-[firmly] No.

635
00:45:52,082 --> 00:45:54,585
You don't get to show up like this
and say something like that

636
00:45:54,668 --> 00:45:56,628
and expect me to be cool with it.

637
00:45:57,504 --> 00:46:01,467
-You're my best friend, asshole.
-I see I was wrong to become your friend.

638
00:46:02,593 --> 00:46:05,888
I... I put you in danger,
and it was selfish of me.

639
00:46:06,638 --> 00:46:10,350
I can't change the past,
but I can stop making the same mistake.

640
00:46:12,311 --> 00:46:15,355
We're done, buddy. It's, uh... It's over.

641
00:46:15,939 --> 00:46:18,233
There's something
seriously wrong with you.

642
00:46:19,318 --> 00:46:20,778
Yeah, I know.

643
00:46:20,861 --> 00:46:23,530
Stay clear of Fisk.
Tell Karen to do the same. And I'd appreciate it
if you didn't tell her you saw me.

644
00:46:26,950 --> 00:46:29,453
-Do you even hear yourself right now?
-Goodbye, Foggy.

645
00:46:29,536 --> 00:46:31,205
Matt! Matt!

646
00:46:32,164 --> 00:46:33,290
[door opens]

647
00:46:35,125 --> 00:46:36,168
[door closes

648
00:46:59,525 --> 00:47:00,984
Was it him?

649
00:47:01,068 --> 00:47:02,861
He took out six feds.

650
00:47:02,945 --> 00:47:06,365
He wasn't in a red suit,
but, yeah, it was him.

651
00:47:15,874 --> 00:47:17,918
So the Devil is back.

